Class LevelParent

    Direct Known Subclasses:
    LevelOne, LevelThree, LevelTwo

    public abstract class LevelParent
extends javax.swing.JPanel
    The LevelParent class is the parent to all 3 levels of the game. It contains essential methods which are used in each level.

    Course Info:

    ICS4U0 - Krasteva, V.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    (Project Manager) Russell Leong, (Project Member) Liam Telenko

      • updateObjectCounter

        public javax.swing.JPanel updateObjectCounter()
        updateObjectCounter updates the green and red icons at the bottom of the panel. The dots represent which objects have been found/still need to be found to proceed in the level.
        Returns:
        JPanel complete with the updated object counter comprising of red and green dots. A red dot represents a still unfound object, green dots represent found objects.
